  "response": "Here are some popular dance club songs that are typically well-received and can get people on the dance floor:\n\n1. **\"Uptown Funk\" - Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars**\n2. **\"Blinding Lights\" - The Weeknd**\n3. **\"Levitating\" - Dua Lipa ft. DaBaby**\n4. **\"Titanium\" - David Guetta ft. Sia**\n5. **\"Don't Start Now\" - Dua Lipa**\n6. **\"I Gotta Feeling\" - The Black Eyed Peas**\n7. **\"Wake Me Up\" - Avicii**\n8. **\"Get Lucky\" - Daft Punk ft. Pharrell Williams**\n9. **\"Taki Taki\" - DJ Snake ft. Selena Gomez, Ozuna, Cardi B**\n10. **\"Party Rock Anthem\" - LMFAO**\n11. **\"Shape of You\" - Ed Sheeran**\n12. **\"Dance Monkey\" - Tones and I**\n13. **\"Roses (Imanbek Remix)\" - SAINt JHN**\n14. **\"Physical\" - Dua Lipa**\n15. **\"Rain On Me\" - Lady Gaga & Ariana Grande**\n\nThese tracks span various genres and years, ensuring a lively atmosphere at any dance club.",
